Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
update_metric(25.10)                                      update_metric(25.10)

Name
       update_metric - Updates a metric

Syntax
       update_metric

       [-help]

       [-format {html excel text}]

       [-graph_type {treemap line none}]

       [-group <group_title>]

       [-header <header_name>]

       [-link_file_metric <metric_name>]

        [-link_table <table>]

       [-metric <metric_name>]

       [-no_shared_max]

       [-renderer <html_format>]

        [-show_graph]

       -table <table_id>

       [-title <html_table_title>]

       Updates a metric.

Parameters
       -format {html excel text}
              Specifies configuration for the specified report_metric format.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -graph_type {treemap line none}
              Specifies  the  type of graph to use in the table (treemap |line
              |none).

              Default: line

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -group <group_title>
              Specifies the group title to be used in the html table.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -header <header_name>
              Specifies the header name to be added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Prints out the command usage. For a detailed description of  the
              command, use the man command: man update_metric

       -metric <metric_name>
              Specifies the metric name to be added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -no_shared_max
              When  specified  for a -renderer histogram metric, the Y axis of
              all the histograms in a single column stop sharing the same  max
              Y value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -link_file_metric <metric_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the metric containing filename to open
              when the metric value is clicked.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -link_table <table>
              Specifies the table to  scroll  to  when  the  metric  value  is
              clicked.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -renderer <html_format>
              Forces a specific html format renderer for the histogram metric.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -show_graph
              Specifies whether to show this metric in a comparison graph.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -table <table_id>
              Specifies the id of table to which the metric will be added.

              Data_type: string, required

       -title <html_table_title>
              Specifies the title to be used in the html table.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following sequence of commands create the table_s metric table and
       update the table using the update_metric command.

       innovus 1> create_metric_page -name User

       innovus 2> create_metric_table_heading -id statistics -page User   -ti-
       tle "Average Timing Values Per Snapshot"

       innovus   3>   create_metric_table   -id  table_s  -heading  statistics
       -per_snapshot -type  horizontal

       innovus 4> update_metric -table table_s -metric  user.avg_slack  -group
       "Timing Statistics" -title avg_slack

       innovus  5> update_metric -table table_s -metric user.arith_mean -group
       "Timing Statistics" -title arith_mean

       innovus 6> update_metric -table table_s -metric  user.geom_mean  -group
       "Timing Statistics" -title geom_mean

       innovus 7> update_metric -table table_s -metric user.rms -group "Timing
       Statistics" -title rms

Related Information
              * report_metric

